20in%20consistency%2C%20and%20it's%20served%20cold%20alongside%20desserts.%20Americans%20might%20know%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bhard%20sauce.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBrits%20say%20%26quot%3BHappy%20Christmas%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20%26quot%3BMerry%20Christmas.%26quot%3B%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224416%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22merry%20christmas%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ddebceb79d7575b76633793%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223312%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BMerry%20Christmas%26quot%3B%20lit-up%20sign.%3Cp%3EJohnnie%20Pakington%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20remember%20a%20scene%20from%20the%20first%20%26quot%3BHarry%20Potter%26quot%3B%20movie%20in%20which%20Ron%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BHappy%20Christmas%2C%20Harry!%26quot%3B%20While%20this%20may%20sound%20strange%20to%20an%20American%2C%20saying%20%26quot%3BHappy%20Christmas%26quot%3B%20is%20commonplace%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20%26quot%3BMerry%20Christmas.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EChristmas%20crackers%20are%20cardboard%20tubes%20wrapped%20in%20brightly%20colored%20paper%20and%5Cntwisted%20at%20each%20end%20that%20two%20people%20pull%20for%20a%20fun%20surprise.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224993%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22christmas%20cracker%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ddebda579d757758848e8f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223745%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGirl%20pulling%20a%20Christmas%20cracker%20at%20the%20dinner%20table.%3Cp%3EPeopleImages%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChristmas%20crackers%20are%20often%20pulled%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20meal%2C%20and%20the%20paper%20hats%20found%20inside%20are%20worn%20throughout%20the%20meal.%20Also%20inside%20each%20cracker%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bbanger%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20makes%20a%20loud%20pop%20when%20the%20cracker%20is%20p